objects.name: goofy guineapig
objects.description: A persistent Windows backdoor with HTTPS C2 communications, capable of collecting and exfiltrating system information and loading additional plugins.

objects.name: T1543.003
objects.description: Create or Modify System Process: Windows Service, used by Goofy Guineapig for persistence.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location, used by Goofy Guineapig to evade detection.

objects.name: T1497.003
objects.description: Virtualization/Sandbox Evasion: Time Based Evasion, used by Goofy Guineapig to evade sandbox detection.

objects.name: T1027.002
objects.description: Obfuscated Files or Information: Software Packing, used by Goofy Guineapig to evade detection.

objects.name: T1564.003
objects.description: Hide Artefacts: Hidden Window, used by Goofy Guineapig to evade detection.

objects.name: T1070.004
objects.description: Indicator Removal on Host: File Deletion, used by Goofy Guineapig to evade detection.

objects.name: T1574.002
objects.description: Hijack Execution Flow: DLL Side-Loading, used by Goofy Guineapig to load the malicious DLL.

objects.name: T1055.012
objects.description: Process Injection: Process Hollowing, used by Goofy Guineapig to inject the malicious payload.

objects.name: T1218.011
objects.description: System Binary Proxy Execution: Rundll32, used by Goofy Guineapig for persistence.

objects.name: T1082
objects.description: System Information Discovery, used by Goofy Guineapig to collect system information.

objects.name: T1071.001
objects.description: Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols, used by Goofy Guineapig for C2 communications.

objects.description: Non-Standard Port, used by Goofy Guineapig for C2 communications over a non-standard port.
